com.mojang.datafixers.kinds

Interface Traversable<T extends K1,Mu extends Traversable _>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The container type.
    Mu - The witness type for this traversable.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Mu<T>, Functor T, Kind1 T
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CartesianLike<T,C,Mu>, CocartesianLike<T,C,Mu>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Either.Instance, ListBox.Instance, OptionalBox.Instance, Pair.Instance

    public interface Traversable<T extends K1,Mu extends Traversable _>
extends Functor T
    The traversable type class for some container type takes in an effectful transformation and produces an equivalent effectful transformation on the container type.

    This type class may be used to e.g. produce a function ListBox<A> -> DataResult<ListBox<B>> from a function A -> DataResult<B>, only producing a successful result if all the original elements were converted successfully.

    Note that the implementation of Functor.map(Function, App) inherited from Functor can be implemented in terms of traverse(Applicative, Function, App) as map(f, ta) = traverse(IdF, f, ta). This interface leaves that method abstract because of the differing function types in Functor.map(Function, App) and traverse(Applicative, Function, App) that make the default implementation outline above impossible without an unchecked (albeit safe) cast.

    See Also:
    Applicative

        Applies a function that produces an Applicative effect to each value contained within input, then builds a container with an equivalent structure containing the (unboxed) results.
        API Note:
        This function defines the traversable operator with the applicative functor F.
        Type Parameters:
